<TITLE> Another top Jamaat leader arrested in Rajshahi </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com)  Another top Jamaat-e-Islami leader of Rajshahi city was arrested Wednesday in connection with Chhatra League activist Faruk Hossain's killing during overnight clashes on Rajshahi University campus on Feb 8-9, police said. Abul Kalam Azad, secretary general of Rajshahi city Jamaat-e-Islami, from his Bongram house at on Wednesday at 4pm, police said. He was arrested on the basis of a statement given by Jamaat-Shibir activists who were earlier arrested in the wake of the campus violence, Tarikul Islam, assistant commissioner of Rajshahi Metropolitan Police Detective Branch, told bdnews24.com. The Jamaat leader is now in custody of Boalia Model Police Station, he said. Faruk died and scores of students sustained injuries during Feb 8-9 clashes between ruling pro-government Bangladesh Chhatra League and Islamic Chhatra Shibir, Jamaat-e-Islami's student wing. Shortly after the incident, the government launched a countrywide operation to round up hundreds of 'Jamaat-Shibir' suspects. Detective Branch police also arrested Tareq Saifullah, former Chhatra Shibir president of Rajshahi Polytechnic Institute, said Boalia police chief Jashim Uddin. He said Tareq is now under their custody and being interrogated over Faruk's killing. Officer in charge at Motihar Police Station Tafazzal Hossain said they also arrested another six Shibir activists on Wednesday. Detective Branch police also arrested Siddique Hossain, principal of Binodpur Islami College and an assistant secretary of Jamaat's Rajshahi city unit, from his Rajpara residence Tuesday evening. Rajshahi's additional chief metropolitan magistrate Ruhul Amin on Wednesday granted police five days' remand to grill him. On Feb 11, Jamaat's Rajshahi city unit amir Maulana Ataur Rahman was arrested for his alleged backing of the RU violence. He was sent to jail on Tuesday after a five-day grilling by police. Assistant police commissioner Tariqul Islam said 82 other Jamaat-Shibir activists were also rounded up in Rajshahi in connection with the case. With the latest, total arrests of Jamaat-Shibir men in Rajshahi stood at 90 up to Wednesday afternoon. bdn
